<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-785-072  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 785 072.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 27 1990 v7 n34 p42(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>High-speed image-processing package debuts. (Data Translation Inc.andO;introduces Global Lab Color software for use with color framegrabber boards) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data Translation Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DATX.andO;Product:   Global Lab Color (Image processing software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Image processingSoftware packagesColorGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Data Translation Inc. recently announced a new software package that letsusers of its color frame-grabber board perform high-speed image processing.andM;Global Lab Color software, due out next month for $1,995, gives users of DataTranslation's DT2871 Color Frame Grabber board the ability to capture 24-bitcolor images and convert them into HSI (hue, saturation and intensity) modeused in high-end image-processing machines, according to Mike Travis, productmarketing manager at the Marlboro, Mass., company.andM;Using the software and frame-grabber board, which plugs into IBM ATs andcompatibles, researchers can analyze complicated image-processingapplications quickly, Travis said.andP;  For example, scientists can use the boardand software to differentiate cells by color, a task that would take morethan twice as long without the board and software, Travis said.andM;Global Lab Color, which requires 1.5M bytes of RAM, performs image processingin 8-bit or 24-bit color and monochrome.andM;Data Translation can be reached at (508) 481-8620.andO;</TEXT></DOC>